#INSTRUCTIONS 
This is for those of you who use Notion/Confluence, Jira, and CI/CD and want to refer to a single source of truth for security checks that looks at Security in the SDLC. 
Machine readable + you can connect your tools to read + refer to this as a starting point. 
This would be complementary to the semgrep ruleset, as well as the cursorrules files you add to your project.
Create a file at repo root: .security-checks.json
Paste the following text, updating details for your IDE, CI, and Jira/Notion environments so all these can read and refer to this as a single source of truth. 


{
  "version": "1.0",
  "categories": [
    {
